                            <comment id="14950093" author="blerer" created="Fri, 9 Oct 2015 08:55:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch for 2.2 is &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/compare/trunk...blerer:10487-2.2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; and the one for 3.0 is &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/compare/trunk...blerer:10487-3.0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I did not find the change that introduced the regression but it seems that the problem was caused by the commands using the &lt;tt&gt;LIMIT&lt;/tt&gt; value to limit the number of rows retrieved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch for &lt;tt&gt;2.2&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;makes sure that for aggregate queries we do not pass the &lt;tt&gt;LIMIT&lt;/tt&gt; value to the commands&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;adds extra unit tests&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fix the &lt;tt&gt;NEWS.txt&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The patch for &lt;tt&gt;3.0&lt;/tt&gt; fix the &lt;tt&gt;NEWS.txt&lt;/tt&gt; and add some extra tests.&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;
&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The unit test results for 2.2 are &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-10487-2.2-testall/1/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The dtest results for 2.2 are &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/blerer/job/blerer-10487-2.2-dtest/1/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
